</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Quantitative easing </strong>- A monetary policy whereby a central bank buys securities to increase the money supply and encourage lending and investment.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Inflation</strong> - The rate at which the general level of prices for goods and services rises, eroding purchasing power.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>Financial stability</strong> - A state in which the economic system, including institutions and markets, operates smoothly without crises.









