</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-66_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The BoE's monetary policy is central to its function, with the base interest rate being a critical tool. Adjusting this rate influences borrowing and spending to achieve price stability and support economic growth. During periods of economic downturn, the BoE may lower interest rates to encourage borrowing and investment, while raising rates can help cool down the economy in times of inflationary pressure.




























