</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-72_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Ensuring financial stability involves proactive measures to monitor and mitigate systemic risks. The FPC plays a crucial role in identifying vulnerabilities within the economic system and implementing policies to address them. This includes setting countercyclical capital buffers for banks, which can be adjusted to ensure financial institutions have enough capital to absorb shocks during economic downturns.





























